1
00:01:21,266 --> 00:01:26,067
[COW MOOS]

2
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:29,533
- MYOGA, MY FRIEND, YOU'D
BETTER NOT BE DECEIVING ME.

3
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:32,948
HAS THIS INU-SOMETHING-OR-OTHER
REALLY MANAGED TO MASTER

4
00:01:32,982 --> 00:01:34,082
THE TETSUSAIGA?

5
00:01:34,115 --> 00:01:38,696
- HIS NAME IS INUYASHA.
- OH, THAT'S RIGHT! INUYASHA.

6
00:01:38,730 --> 00:01:42,030
HE'S THE SON OF THE GREAT
DOG DEMON WHO GAVE ME HIS FANG

7
00:01:42,063 --> 00:01:44,043
SO THAT I COULD FORGE
A SWORD FROM IT.

8
00:01:44,076 --> 00:01:45,827
HE'S THE RUNT OF THE LITTER,
CORRECT?

9
00:01:45,861 --> 00:01:47,266
- YES. HE'S THE YOUNGER BROTHER,

10
00:01:47,299 --> 00:01:48,766
AND YOU'D BETTER
LEARN SOME RESPECT.

11
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:53,399
I'VE SEEN HIM KILL 100 DEMONS
WITH ONE SWING OF HIS SWORD.

12
00:01:53,432 --> 00:01:56,799
- I WON'T BE ACCUSED
OF ABANDONING YOU.

13
00:01:56,832 --> 00:01:58,899
I DON'T WANT NO GUILT TRIP.

14
00:01:58,932 --> 00:02:02,233
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LAY
THAT RESPONSIBILITY ON ME!

15
00:02:03,827 --> 00:02:06,227
AAH!

16
00:02:10,608 --> 00:02:12,849
- MIND YOU,
I'VE ONLY SEE HIM DO IT ONCE,

17
00:02:12,882 --> 00:02:15,443
AND HE HASN'T BEEN ABLE
TO WIELD THAT POWER SINCE.

18
00:02:15,476 --> 00:02:21,917
- PERHAPS IT IS BECAUSE HE DOES
NOT DESERVE TO USE THE FAMOUS
TETSUSAIGA THAT I FORGED.

19
00:02:22,583 --> 00:02:26,984
I SUPPOSE I WILL HAVE TO TEST
HIS WORTH SOMEHOW.

20
00:02:34,305 --> 00:02:37,572
[WOLF HOWLS]

21
00:02:46,073 --> 00:02:49,906
- HH-HOT! OOH OOH! OH OH! YAII!

22
00:02:49,940 --> 00:02:52,406
- WHAT KIND OF HELLHOLE
IS THIS PLACE?

23
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:54,173
THE ROCKS UNDER MY FEET ARE RED.

24
00:02:54,206 --> 00:02:56,606
MM! I SMELL
ROASTING MEAT SOMEWHERE.

25
00:02:56,640 --> 00:03:00,406
HMM? OOH! EEH!

26
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:03,140
[WHIMPERING]

27
00:03:03,173 --> 00:03:06,406
[SIZZLES]
- WHOA! OW!

28
00:03:07,606 --> 00:03:10,273
[PANTING]

29
00:03:10,306 --> 00:03:11,406
HUH?

30
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,406
HMM. THIS MUST BE IT.

31
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,640
ARE YOU HERE TOTO-SAI?

32
00:03:14,673 --> 00:03:17,206
I HOPE YOU FINISHED THE SWORD
YOU WERE COMMISSIONED TO FORGE.

33
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:20,340
THIS IS THE PROMISED
DATE OF DELIVERY.

34
00:03:21,706 --> 00:03:25,773
HMM. HEY, COME ON OUT!
I'M TALKING TO YOU.

35
00:03:25,806 --> 00:03:27,306
HUH? OH!

36
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:30,640
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'VE MOVED?

37
00:03:30,673 --> 00:03:32,973
DAMN THAT SNEAKY BADGER.

38
00:03:33,006 --> 00:03:35,540
WHERE'D HE GO?
WHERE'D HE GO?

39
00:03:35,573 --> 00:03:38,473
WHOA...

40
00:03:38,506 --> 00:03:41,306
- SO, TOTO-SAI IS GONE.

41
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:42,873
- PLEASE FORGIVE ME,
MASTER SESSHO-MARU,

42
00:03:42,906 --> 00:03:45,873
BUT THAT ERICAN SWORDSMITH IS
KNOWN TO BE VERY TEMPERAMENTAL,

43
00:03:45,906 --> 00:03:51,306
AND HE ONLY FORGES SWORDS
IF HE TAKES A PERSONAL LIKING
TO THE CUSTOMER WHO ORDERED IT.

44
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:56,806
- I SEE.
HE HAS NO INTENTION OF FORGING
A SWORD THAT SUITS MY PURPOSE,

45
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:58,306
AND SO HE HAS ESCAPED.

46
00:03:58,340 --> 00:04:00,206
- YOU CAN'T BLAME HIM
FOR NOT LIKING YOU.

47
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:05,406
YOUR RESUME IS ONE LONG
DEATH WISH. UHH! HUHH!

48
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,140
AAH! YOU'RE SMILING.

49
00:04:08,173 --> 00:04:10,406
OH, DON'T SMILE AT ME,
MASTER SESSHO-MARU.

50
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,806
PLEASE GET ANGRY.

51
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,706
YOU'RE ALWAYS MUCH HARDER
ON ME WHEN YOU'RE BEING
PASSIVE-AGGRESSIVE.

52
00:04:14,740 --> 00:04:18,006
PLEASE BE STRAIGHT
WITH ME, PLEASE!

53
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,040
HMM?

54
00:04:20,432 --> 00:04:24,253
I THINK I'VE JUST SHORTENED
MY LIFE BY 100 YEARS.

55
00:04:32,613 --> 00:04:37,347
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
MY JEWEL SHARDS WERE TAKEN.

56
00:04:37,980 --> 00:04:40,813
[GASPS]

57
00:04:42,813 --> 00:04:44,280
- STOP WORRYING
ABOUT IT, KAGOME.

58
00:04:44,574 --> 00:04:47,975
- BUT...
- IT'S NOT LIKE SHE STOLE
ALL THE PIECES OR NOTHING.

59
00:04:48,008 --> 00:04:49,749
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO GO OUT
AND FIND SOME MORE.

60
00:04:49,783 --> 00:04:51,649
NO BIG DEAL.
- HMM.

61
00:04:52,444 --> 00:04:56,345
- WHY IS INUYASHA BEING
SO UNDERSTANDING?
IT'S SO UNLIKE HIM.

62
00:04:56,378 --> 00:05:00,745
- I SUSPECT IT IS BECAUSE
KIKYO WAS THE ONE WHO STOLE
THE SACRED JEWEL SHARDS.

63
00:05:00,778 --> 00:05:03,745
- OH, WHAT CAN HE DO
WHEN THE CULPRIT IS A WOMAN
HE'S BEEN IN LOVE WITH?

64
00:05:03,778 --> 00:05:08,379
- LISTEN, YOU MORONS, IF YOU
THINK I'M PROTECTING KIKYO,
YOU'VE GOT ANOTHER THING COMING!

65
00:05:08,413 --> 00:05:10,046
OK?!

66
00:05:10,838 --> 00:05:13,143
YOU THINK I'M GOING
SOFT ON HER, TOO, DON'T YOU?

67
00:05:13,176 --> 00:05:14,343
THEN SPEAK UP!

68
00:05:15,417 --> 00:05:18,778
[GROWLS]
YOU GOT SOMETHING TO SAY,
THEN SAY IT TO MY FACE!

69
00:05:18,812 --> 00:05:21,245
[COW MOOS]
- HUH?

70
00:05:21,278 --> 00:05:23,112
- A COW?
- WHERE IS IT?

71
00:05:23,145 --> 00:05:25,345
I DON'T SEE ANY CATTLE
AROUND HERE.

72
00:05:25,378 --> 00:05:28,845
[MOOING]
- HUH?
[GASP]

73
00:05:28,878 --> 00:05:31,145
- IN THE SKY?!

74
00:05:32,078 --> 00:05:33,378
- AAH!

75
00:05:33,412 --> 00:05:34,778
- WHAT'S GOING ON?

76
00:05:35,449 --> 00:05:39,449
- INUYASHA!
- WHO THE HECK ARE YOU?

77
00:05:39,482 --> 00:05:44,015
- MY NAME IS TOTO-SAI.
DRAW YOUR SWORD, INUYASHA.

78
00:05:44,049 --> 00:05:46,449
- HOW DOES THAT OLD GEEZER
KNOW MY NAME?

79
00:05:46,482 --> 00:05:50,582
- I'M COMING AT YOU WHETHER
YOU PUT UP YOUR SWORD OR NOT!

80
00:05:50,615 --> 00:05:53,149
HAAH!
- GET BACK, KAGOME.

81
00:05:53,182 --> 00:05:55,982
- OK.
- UHH!

82
00:05:56,015 --> 00:05:58,249
[GRUNTING]

83
00:05:59,282 --> 00:06:00,715
HUH?

84
00:06:02,449 --> 00:06:05,082
- HE THWARTED THE TETSUSAIGA
USING A HAMMER?

85
00:06:05,115 --> 00:06:08,315
- OOH! THAT SWORD IS SINGING
LIKE AN OLD SAW--

86
00:06:08,349 --> 00:06:12,849
DULL RESONANCE--THIS KID CAN'T
BE THE RIGHT ONE TO USE IT!

87
00:06:12,882 --> 00:06:16,515
- TELL ME WHO THE HELL YOU ARE!

88
00:06:19,212 --> 00:06:20,262
AAH!

89
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:22,329
HUH?
- HE STOPPED THE SWORD.

90
00:06:22,362 --> 00:06:24,143
- THAT'S A PIECE OF LEATHER.

91
00:06:24,176 --> 00:06:27,543
- YOU'VE BEEN TOO ROUGH
WITH HER; THIS BLADE IS
ALL NICKED UP.

92
00:06:27,576 --> 00:06:31,743
HAVE YOU BEEN
CHOPPING DOWN TREES? HMM.

93
00:06:31,776 --> 00:06:35,109
- WHAT DO YOU KNOW ABOUT IT?
WHO ARE YOU?

94
00:06:35,143 --> 00:06:37,376
- I THINK THAT'S ENOUGH,
TOTO-SAI.

95
00:06:37,409 --> 00:06:39,109
- HUH? MYOGA?

96
00:06:39,143 --> 00:06:42,576
SO YOU'RE THE SWORDSMITH
WHO FORGED TETSUSAIGA?

97
00:06:42,609 --> 00:06:44,009
- PRECISELY!

98
00:06:44,043 --> 00:06:48,409
I'M THE MAN WHO FORGED
TETSUSAIGA FROM A FANG
THAT YOUR FATHER GAVE TO ME.

99
00:06:48,443 --> 00:06:56,244
ONLY CERTAIN CIRCLES OF THE
FINEST BLADE-SWINGING DEMONS
ARE ACQUAINTED WITH MY WORK.

100
00:06:56,277 --> 00:06:58,858
- HUH? CERTAIN CIRCLES?

101
00:06:58,892 --> 00:07:02,092
- I THINK THAT'S A POLITE WAY
OF SAYING HE'S NOT VERY FAMOUS.

102
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:05,158
- I DON'T GIVE A RAT'S ASS IF
YOU'RE FAMOUS OR NOT, OLD MAN!

103
00:07:05,192 --> 00:07:08,025
- WELL, NOW THAT I'VE SEEN
THE TETSUSAIGA IN ACTION,

104
00:07:08,058 --> 00:07:12,692
I HAVE TO SAY THE SWORD IS BEING
BADLY MISUSED AND ABUSED.

105
00:07:12,725 --> 00:07:14,358
IT SINGS A SAD SONG INDEED.

106
00:07:14,392 --> 00:07:19,092
TO SEE MY WORK LIKE THIS,
OH, IT SIMPLY BREAKS MY HEART.

107
00:07:19,125 --> 00:07:22,492
- IF YOU'VE COME TO PICK A FIGHT
WITH ME, JUST SAY SO.

108
00:07:22,525 --> 00:07:23,358
- INUYASHA!

109
00:07:23,392 --> 00:07:25,625
- OH, THIS IS USELESS, MYOGA.

110
00:07:25,658 --> 00:07:28,458
THE TETSUSAIGA CAN'T BE
ENTRUSTED TO SOMEONE
AS SHORT-TEMPERED

111
00:07:28,492 --> 00:07:31,258
AS THIS ARROGANT WHELP.
- I SEE WHAT YOU MEAN.

112
00:07:31,292 --> 00:07:34,192
IT WOULD PROBABLY BE BETTER
IF HE JUST GAVE UP THE SWORD,

113
00:07:34,225 --> 00:07:35,792
THAN RECKLESSLY GOING
INTO BATTLE WITH IT,

114
00:07:35,825 --> 00:07:40,725
BLINDLY TRYING TO RELY
ON A STRENGTH HE DOESN'T HAVE
THE SELF-DISCIPLINE TO YIELD.

115
00:07:40,758 --> 00:07:41,858
- YES, THERE'S NO USE STALLING.

116
00:07:41,892 --> 00:07:44,558
I'LL HAVE TO TAKE
THE TETSUSAIGA BACK IMMEDIATELY

117
00:07:44,592 --> 00:07:47,592
AND BREAK IT IN HALF.
- WHAT DID YOU SAY?

118
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:50,458
I DON'T CARE WHO MADE
THIS SWORD, YOU DRIED-UP
METAL BENDER.

119
00:07:50,492 --> 00:07:54,358
IT'S MINE, AND I'LL RUN YOU
THROUGH WITH IT IF YOU EVEN
TRY TO BREAK IT!

120
00:07:54,392 --> 00:07:56,992
- I DON'T HAVE TO BREAK IT.
IT WAS ONLY A THOUGHT.

121
00:07:57,025 --> 00:08:00,992
[SIGHS]
- SORRY. I FORGOT TO
WARN YOU ABOUT HIS TEMPER.

122
00:08:01,025 --> 00:08:03,225
- DON'T WORRY.
I'LL SNEAK IT AWAY
WHEN HE'S NOT LOOKING

123
00:08:03,258 --> 00:08:06,740
AND MELT IT INTO CUTLERY.
AAH! I--I'M ONLY JOKING.

124
00:08:06,773 --> 00:08:12,594
- MASTER INUYASHA, YOU HAVEN'T
BEEN ABLE TO UNRAVEL THE MYSTERY
OF THE TETSUSAIGA ON YOUR OWN.

125
00:08:12,619 --> 00:08:14,652
YOU'VE TRIED, BUT YOU CAN'T
FIGURE OUT HOW TO TAP INTO

126
00:08:14,685 --> 00:08:17,819
THE POWER THAT KILLED
THE 100 DEMONS IN ONE SWEEP.

127
00:08:17,852 --> 00:08:19,285
BUT TOTO-SAI KNOWS ITS SECRET.

128
00:08:19,319 --> 00:08:22,852
I THINK IF YOU BOTH TOOK
THE TIME TO GET TO KNOW
ONE ANOTHER AND COOPERATE,

129
00:08:22,885 --> 00:08:26,319
YOU COULD AWAKEN AND HARNESS
TETSUSAIGA'S FULL STRENGTH.

130
00:08:26,352 --> 00:08:29,185
- THERE'S NO MYSTERY.
I'LL GET THE HANG OF IT.

131
00:08:29,219 --> 00:08:30,652
I JUST NEED PRACTICE.

132
00:08:30,685 --> 00:08:34,085
- I UNDERSTAND YOU'VE BEEN
COLLECTING THE SACRED
JEWEL SHARDS FOR A WHILE.

133
00:08:34,119 --> 00:08:38,452
WHO KNOWS HOW MANY DEMONS
HAVE MULTIPLE PIECES
OF THE JEWEL?

134
00:08:38,485 --> 00:08:43,185
YOU KNOW HOW DIFFICULT
IT'S BEEN TO BATTLE DEMONS
WITH MORE THAN ONE.

135
00:08:43,219 --> 00:08:46,219
DON'T YOU WANT TO AWAKEN
THE TETSUSAIGA'S FULL POTENTIAL

136
00:08:46,252 --> 00:08:49,819
IN ORDER TO DESTROY DEMONS
WITH THAT ENHANCED STRENGTH?

137
00:08:49,852 --> 00:08:51,752
- HE DOES HAVE A POINT,
INUYASHA.

138
00:08:51,785 --> 00:08:54,819
- I THINK YOU SHOULD AT LEAST
HEAR WHAT HE HAS TO SAY.

139
00:08:54,852 --> 00:08:57,852
- I GUESS IT CAN'T HURT.
[GRUNTS]

140
00:08:57,885 --> 00:09:00,952
SO, TELL ME, WHAT DO
I HAVE TO DO, TOTO-SAI?

141
00:09:00,985 --> 00:09:04,285
- FIRST, I HAVE TO TELL YOU
THAT SOMEONE SEEKS MY LIFE.

142
00:09:04,319 --> 00:09:06,019
- HUH?

143
00:09:06,052 --> 00:09:10,219
- A FOOL BARGED INTO MY FORGE
AND ORDERED A SWORD THAT WOULD
RIVAL THE POWER OF TETSUSAIGA.

144
00:09:10,252 --> 00:09:12,619
HE TOLD ME HE'D KILL ME
IF I REFUSED.

145
00:09:12,652 --> 00:09:16,619
I WANT YOU TO PROTECT ME
FROM HIM.

146
00:09:16,652 --> 00:09:19,652
- SAY PLEASE BEFORE
ASKING FOR FAVORS.

147
00:09:19,685 --> 00:09:21,585
- YOU NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT THIS.

148
00:09:21,619 --> 00:09:23,152
WHAT DID HE LOOK LIKE?

149
00:09:23,185 --> 00:09:28,119
- HE HAS LONG, WHITE HAIR,
AND HE WEARS A CLOAK MADE OF
SOMETHING WHITE AND FURRY.

150
00:09:28,152 --> 00:09:30,185
- WHAT? ANOTHER OLD GEEZER?

151
00:09:30,219 --> 00:09:32,719
[RASPBERRY]
- GUESS AGAIN!

152
00:09:32,752 --> 00:09:34,185
- WAIT A MINUTE.

153
00:09:34,219 --> 00:09:37,852
IF HE'S YOUNG, DRESSED
IN FUR, AND WANTS A SWORD
STRONGER THAN TETSUSAIGA,

154
00:09:37,885 --> 00:09:42,285
COULD HE BE...?
- HE--HE--HE'S HERE.

155
00:09:42,319 --> 00:09:44,119
- HUH?

156
00:09:46,819 --> 00:09:49,319
SESSHO-MARU.

157
00:09:52,452 --> 00:09:56,052
- WHO IS THAT?
- INUYASHA'S OLDER BROTHER.

158
00:09:56,085 --> 00:09:59,419
- I WAS RIGHT.
HE IS THE ONE WHO'S AFTER YOU.

159
00:09:59,452 --> 00:10:01,552
- EXACTLY!
SO PROTECT ME!

160
00:10:01,585 --> 00:10:06,985
- INUYASHA, WHY HAVE YOU
CONSPIRED WITH TOTO-SAI
TO PLOT AGAINST ME?

161
00:10:07,019 --> 00:10:09,985
- BECAUSE YOU HAPPEN
TO BE EVIL INCARNATE?

162
00:10:10,019 --> 00:10:14,952
- TOTO-SAI, IT SOUNDS LIKE
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR AN EARLY
RETIREMENT INTO YOUR GRAVE.

163
00:10:14,985 --> 00:10:17,385
- I--I NEVER SAID I WAS
TALKING ABOUT YOU, SESSHO-MARU!

164
00:10:17,419 --> 00:10:22,652
WHY DON'T WE DISCUSS
YOUR SWORD AFTER YOU BATTLE
IT OUT WITH INUYASHA?

165
00:10:22,685 --> 00:10:24,385
- YOU SURE CHANGED YOUR TUNE
PRETTY QUICK.

166
00:10:24,419 --> 00:10:28,385
YOU'RE NOT BIG ON LOYALTY.
- DID I? I DON'T REMEMBER.

167
00:10:28,419 --> 00:10:29,485
- UHH!

168
00:10:29,519 --> 00:10:34,319
- TOTO-SAI, YOUR WORD IS AS GOOD
AS A BLOOD VOW TO ME.

169
00:10:34,352 --> 00:10:36,252
DID YOU HEAR THAT,
INUYASHA?

170
00:10:36,285 --> 00:10:39,852
HE WILL FORGE MY NEW SWORD
AFTER I KILL YOU OFF.

171
00:10:39,885 --> 00:10:45,252
- KAGOME, RUN FOR COVER.
[GASPING]

172
00:10:48,252 --> 00:10:51,452
- OH, YEAH?
WE'LL SEE WHO KILLS WHO!

173
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:53,652
YAAAH!

174
00:10:55,385 --> 00:10:57,919
- YOU CAN TELL BY THEIR TEMPERS
THEY'RE RELATED.

175
00:10:57,952 --> 00:11:00,419
- YOU'RE THE ONE WHO STARTED
THIS WHOLE THING.

176
00:11:00,452 --> 00:11:03,285
[GASPS]
- DID I, REALLY?

177
00:11:03,319 --> 00:11:04,052
- HUH!

178
00:11:04,085 --> 00:11:05,552
NO WONDER HE'S PALS
WITH MYOGA.

179
00:11:05,585 --> 00:11:08,319
THEY'RE BOTH REAL PROS
WITH THE INNOCENT BYSTANDER ACT.

180
00:11:08,352 --> 00:11:12,919
WHERE IS MYOGA?
MYOGA, ARE YOU HERE?

181
00:11:13,185 --> 00:11:15,085
- KAGOME, HE'S
ON MIROKU'S SHOULDER.

182
00:11:15,119 --> 00:11:16,585
HE ALWAYS GOES
WHERE IT'S SAFEST.

183
00:11:16,619 --> 00:11:18,752
THAT MEANS IT'S DANGEROUS
OVER THERE.

184
00:11:18,785 --> 00:11:22,252
- WHAT? OH, NO!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING? LET GO!

185
00:11:22,285 --> 00:11:26,785
[GASPS]
HEY! YOU COWARD!

186
00:11:28,885 --> 00:11:30,985
[GRUNTING]

187
00:11:37,852 --> 00:11:39,319
- HUH?

188
00:11:40,952 --> 00:11:42,552
- TOO SLOW.

189
00:11:42,585 --> 00:11:44,219
[GRUNTING]

190
00:11:44,252 --> 00:11:46,885
[COUGHS]

191
00:11:51,652 --> 00:11:52,419
[ALL GASP]

192
00:11:52,452 --> 00:11:53,919
- INUYASHA'S SO SLOW.
HE'S PATHETIC.

193
00:11:53,952 --> 00:11:58,333
MYOGA, WHY DID YOU LIE TO ME
ABOUT HIS ABILITY TO USE
TETSUSAIGA'S FULL POWER?

194
00:11:58,367 --> 00:12:00,067
- HE USED IT ONCE.
I PROMISE.

195
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,467
- MYOGA DIDN'T LIE.

196
00:12:01,500 --> 00:12:04,367
INUYASHA ALWAYS ENDS UP
SENDING SESSHO-MARU HOME

197
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:06,267
WITH HIS TAIL BETWEEN HIS LEGS.

198
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:10,633
- ARE YOU SURE YOU WEREN'T
DREAMING WHEN YOU SAW HIM
DO THIS, YOUNG LADY?

199
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,000
- HAH!
- UHH! OOH.

200
00:12:12,033 --> 00:12:14,167
- I'M NOT DREAMING IT UP.
IT'S TRUE!

201
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:17,333
- MY APOLOGIES.
- WELL, TOTO-SAI...

202
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:20,300
DON'T YOU FEEL SORRY
FOR TETSUSAIGA?

203
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:23,400
THAT FAMOUS SWORD IS NO BETTER
THAN A WOODEN CLUB

204
00:12:23,433 --> 00:12:26,267
THE WAY INUYASHA SWINGS IT
AROUND LIKE A NEANDERTHAL.

205
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:31,433
A SWORD CAN LIVE OR DIE
DEPENDING ON ITS MASTER.

206
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:35,733
- MM-HMM.
A WISE OBSERVATION, I AGREE.

207
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,900
- STOP AGREEING WITH HIM!

208
00:12:37,933 --> 00:12:39,433
- DON'T GIVE ME THAT,
SWORDSMITH,

209
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,933
OR YOU'LL REALLY HAVE
SOMETHING TO WORRY ABOUT.

210
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:43,233
I'M ONLY WARMING UP.

211
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:47,200
DON'T BE TOO SHOCKED
WHEN YOU SEE WHAT KIND
OF POWER I REALLY GOT!

212
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:48,367
HYAH!

213
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:50,500
[GRUNTING]

214
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,133
- OH, GREAT.
THE BLOOD'S RUSHED TO HIS HEAD.

215
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:58,767
THAT'S ALWAYS BAD NEWS.

216
00:13:01,567 --> 00:13:07,508
- WELL, TOTO-SAI, TELL ME,
DO YOU STILL REFUSE
TO MAKE ME A SWORD?

217
00:13:07,541 --> 00:13:10,841
- HMM...NO WAY!

218
00:13:13,374 --> 00:13:14,874
- YAAH!

219
00:13:15,941 --> 00:13:19,841
- THAT WAS A BIG HELP! HUH?

220
00:13:20,608 --> 00:13:23,641
- SO, YOU ABSOLUTELY REFUSE?

221
00:13:23,674 --> 00:13:26,808
- HMM! BE QUIET,
YOU UNGRATEFUL MONGREL!

222
00:13:26,841 --> 00:13:31,608
YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO
I'VE ALREADY MADE YOU
AN EXCELLENT SWORD.

223
00:13:31,641 --> 00:13:32,674
- HUH?

224
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:36,589
- THE FAMOUS SWORD THAT
YOU NOW WEAR--THE TENSEIGA.

225
00:13:36,622 --> 00:13:40,963
I ALSO FORGED IT FROM A FANG
GIVEN TO ME BY YOUR FATHER.

226
00:13:40,996 --> 00:13:45,757
HE CLEARLY INSTRUCTED
THAT THE ELDEST BROTHER
WOULD HAVE THE TENSEIGA,

227
00:13:45,790 --> 00:13:48,651
AND THE YOUNGEST BROTHER
WOULD HAVE THE TETSUSAIGA.

228
00:13:48,685 --> 00:13:50,606
THAT WAS YOUR FATHER'S
LAST WISH.

229
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:51,972
IT IS A GREAT SWORD OF SWORDS,

230
00:13:52,006 --> 00:13:54,772
NO BETTER AND NO WORSE
THAN THE TETSUSAIGA.

231
00:13:54,806 --> 00:13:56,539
YOU SHOULD LEARN
TO RESPECT AND LOVE IT.

232
00:13:56,572 --> 00:13:59,206
- SO THAT OLD MAN ALSO MADE
SESSHO-MARU'S SWORD?

233
00:13:59,239 --> 00:14:03,572
- THOUGH, COME TO THINK OF IT,
I'VE NEVER SEEN SESSHO-MARU
UNSHEATHE HIS SWORD

234
00:14:03,606 --> 00:14:06,439
IN ANY OF THEIR BATTLES YET.
HAVE YOU?

235
00:14:06,472 --> 00:14:07,639
- NO. YOU'RE RIGHT.

236
00:14:07,672 --> 00:14:13,606
- DO YOU DARE IMPLY THAT THIS
USELESS SWORD IS WORTHY OF ME?

237
00:14:14,506 --> 00:14:18,472
- OHH! I'VE MADE YOU ANGRY,
HAVE I? HA HA HA!

238
00:14:18,506 --> 00:14:23,639
TIME TO TAKE OUR LEAVE.
AAH!

239
00:14:45,039 --> 00:14:47,906
- THEY'VE ESCAPED.

240
00:14:49,153 --> 00:14:52,656
- WOW! I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU HAD THAT KIND OF POWER.

241
00:14:52,689 --> 00:14:54,923
- I'LL SAY.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

242
00:14:54,956 --> 00:14:59,023
INUYASHA SHOULD BE
ASKING YOU FOR PROTECTION,
NOT THE OTHER WAY AROUND.

243
00:14:59,056 --> 00:15:01,756
- YOU TRYING TO SAY
THAT I'M A WEAKLING?!

244
00:15:01,789 --> 00:15:03,523
[SIGHS]
- HMM?

245
00:15:03,556 --> 00:15:06,223
- SESSHO-MARU CALLS
HIS GREAT SWORD USELESS,

246
00:15:06,256 --> 00:15:09,956
AND INUYASHA IS USELESS
WITH HIS GREAT SWORD.

247
00:15:09,989 --> 00:15:12,723
HOW I OVERESTIMATED
BOTH OF THEM.

248
00:15:12,756 --> 00:15:14,689
- WHAT'S THAT?!

249
00:15:14,723 --> 00:15:16,523
[PUNCHES LAND]

250
00:15:16,556 --> 00:15:17,889
- UHH...

251
00:15:17,923 --> 00:15:19,589
- I AM NOT USELESS!

252
00:15:19,623 --> 00:15:22,823
- TOTO-SAI, I'VE BEEN THINKING
ABOUT SESSHO-MARU'S SWORD.

253
00:15:22,856 --> 00:15:26,823
IS IT REALLY AS POWERFUL AS
THE TETSUSAIGA, LIKE YOU SAID?

254
00:15:26,856 --> 00:15:27,923
- THE TENSEIGA?

255
00:15:27,956 --> 00:15:31,223
ITS ABILITIES ARE UNLIKE
ANYTHING I'VE HEARD OF BEFORE.

256
00:15:31,256 --> 00:15:34,456
WHEN YOUR FATHER FIRST
COMMISSIONED ME TO MAKE IT,

257
00:15:34,489 --> 00:15:38,523
I SHUDDERED AT THE VERY THOUGHT
OF ITS IMMENSE POWERS.

258
00:15:38,556 --> 00:15:40,156
- IT'S A BLADE THAT DOESN'T CUT?

259
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:43,089
SO HOW ARE YOU SUPPOSED
TO FIGHT WITH A SWORD LIKE THAT?

260
00:15:43,123 --> 00:15:47,123
- THE TENSEIGA IS NOT A SWORD
USED AGAINST FOES.

261
00:15:47,156 --> 00:15:50,289
TO PUT IT SIMPLY:
IT IS A SWORD OF HEALING.

262
00:15:50,323 --> 00:15:51,389
- HEALING?

263
00:15:51,423 --> 00:15:54,364
- THE TETSUSAIGA IS A SWORD
THAT DEFEATS THE POWERFUL,

264
00:15:54,397 --> 00:15:59,831
AND THE TENSEIGA IS A SWORD
THAT HAS THE ABILITY TO SAVE
THE LIVES OF THE WEAK.

265
00:15:59,864 --> 00:16:01,097
- IT SAVES LIVES?

266
00:16:01,131 --> 00:16:03,997
- IF THE BEARER TRULY
HAS KINDNESS OF HEART
TOWARDS HUMANITY,

267
00:16:04,031 --> 00:16:09,164
THEN THE TENSEIGA HAS THE POWER
TO SAVE 100 PEOPLE IN ONE SWEEP.

268
00:16:09,197 --> 00:16:10,631
- KINDNESS OF HEART?

269
00:16:10,664 --> 00:16:13,964
- SO, THE TETSUSAIGA CAN SLAY
100 DEMONS IN ONE SWEEP,

270
00:16:13,997 --> 00:16:17,131
AND THE TENSEIGA CAN SAVE
100 PEOPLE IN ONE SWEEP?

271
00:16:17,164 --> 00:16:20,664
- BUT HOW ARE YOU ABLE
TO USE THIS SWORD AS A WEAPON?

272
00:16:20,697 --> 00:16:23,264
- IT MUST HAVE THE ABILITY
TO BRING BACK DEAD SOULS.

273
00:16:23,297 --> 00:16:27,164
SUCH A POWER COULD BE
VERY USEFUL DURING
THESE FEUDAL TIMES.

274
00:16:27,197 --> 00:16:30,264
- I ALMOST CALLED THE SWORD
THE COFFIN-CHEATER,

275
00:16:30,297 --> 00:16:31,864
BUT I OPTED FOR
TENSEIGA INSTEAD.

276
00:16:31,897 --> 00:16:37,931
IT WAS A LITTLE MORE CLASSY.
ACTUALLY, IT WAS YOUR FATHER
WHO SUGGESTED THE NAME.

277
00:16:37,964 --> 00:16:42,197
- I GET IT NOW.
NO WONDER SESSHO-MARU
WANTS A NEW SWORD.

278
00:16:42,231 --> 00:16:43,597
HE CAN'T USE HIS.

279
00:16:43,631 --> 00:16:48,464
HE'S INCAPABLE OF FEELING
KINDNESS FOR PEOPLE,
LET ALONE SAVING LIVES.

280
00:16:48,497 --> 00:16:50,331
- TOO BAD THIS ISN'T WORKING.

281
00:16:50,364 --> 00:16:52,685
IT WAS YOUR FATHER'S
LAST WISH, AFTER ALL.

282
00:16:52,718 --> 00:16:54,052
- YOUR BROTHER'S
SO BLACK-HEARTED.

283
00:16:54,085 --> 00:16:58,485
- HE WOULDN'T BE HAPPY
WITH THE SWORD EVEN
IF HE COULD USE IT.

284
00:16:58,518 --> 00:17:00,185
- THAT SMELLS GOOD.

285
00:17:00,218 --> 00:17:02,852
- OH, WELL, ROASTED PIG, INDEED!

286
00:17:02,885 --> 00:17:06,652
LET'S DIG IN, FOLKS.

287
00:17:06,685 --> 00:17:07,885
[ALL GASP]

288
00:17:07,918 --> 00:17:09,818
- HEY! DON'T EAT
THE WHOLE THING, PIG!

289
00:17:09,852 --> 00:17:13,018
- HUH? WHERE'D THE ROAST GO?
- IT'S IN YOUR GREEDY GUT!

290
00:17:13,052 --> 00:17:16,918
- WHERE AM I RIGHT NOW?
WHO ARE YOU PEOPLE?

291
00:17:16,952 --> 00:17:19,585
[CRASH]
- OOMPH!

292
00:17:28,652 --> 00:17:30,152
[HOOTING]

293
00:17:30,185 --> 00:17:34,485
- I DIDN'T REALIZE THAT
YOUR SWORD WAS ALSO YOUR
INHERITANCE FROM YOUR FATHER.

294
00:17:34,518 --> 00:17:38,459
WHY DON'T YOU USE IT, MASTER?
WHAT KIND OF POWER DOES IT HAVE?

295
00:17:38,493 --> 00:17:42,093
OOH, IT MUST BE
SOMETHING REMARKABLE!

296
00:17:42,293 --> 00:17:44,193
- YOU WANT TO KNOW, JAKEN?

297
00:17:44,226 --> 00:17:48,959
- THE IDEA OF 2 SWORDS FORGED
FROM YOUR FATHER'S FANGS
IS EXTREMELY INTRIGUING.

298
00:17:48,993 --> 00:17:52,293
IT'S LIKE THE SWORDS
ARE 2 BROTHERS BORN
FROM THE SAME FATHER,

299
00:17:52,326 --> 00:17:54,526
YET ONE IS POWERFUL
AND ONE IS USELESS.

300
00:17:54,559 --> 00:17:57,326
AAH! I DON'T MEAN YOU'RE
USELESS, MASTER SESSHO-MARU!

301
00:17:57,359 --> 00:18:00,493
I MEAN YOUR SWORD WAS,
OR AT LEAST I DON'T
SEE YOU USING IT,

302
00:18:00,526 --> 00:18:03,193
AND YET THAT HALF-BREED BROTHER
OF YOURS CAN USE HIS,

303
00:18:03,226 --> 00:18:04,826
WHICH MAKES HIM MORE POWERFUL.

304
00:18:04,859 --> 00:18:06,159
OH, BUT DON'T TAKE THAT
PERSONALLY!

305
00:18:06,193 --> 00:18:08,959
I'M SURE--
- JAKEN.
- YES, SIR?

306
00:18:08,993 --> 00:18:11,859
[WHIMPERING]

307
00:18:16,593 --> 00:18:21,159
MASTER SESSHO-MARU, WHY?

308
00:18:31,693 --> 00:18:35,759
- GET UP, JAKEN.
YOU'RE FINE.

309
00:18:35,793 --> 00:18:38,459
- HUH?

310
00:18:40,093 --> 00:18:41,414
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

311
00:18:42,135 --> 00:18:46,869
YOU JUST CUT ME IN HALF.
HOW CAN I BE ALIVE?

312
00:18:46,902 --> 00:18:48,969
- YOU SEE NOW.

313
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:52,669
THIS USELESS TENSEIGA
CANNOT KILL.

314
00:18:52,702 --> 00:18:55,702
- WHAT'S IT GOOD FOR, THEN?

315
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:58,302
[WHIMPERING]

316
00:18:58,335 --> 00:19:00,702
WHAT'S GOING ON?

317
00:19:01,469 --> 00:19:03,702
[GROWLS]

318
00:19:03,735 --> 00:19:06,869
- AAH! A DRAGON!

319
00:19:06,902 --> 00:19:10,183
- WHY DID MY FATHER BESTOW
THIS USELESS TENSEIGA ON ME,

320
00:19:10,216 --> 00:19:13,777
AND YET BLESS INUYASHA
WITH THE TETSUSAIGA?

321
00:19:14,344 --> 00:19:16,044
[GROWLS]

322
00:19:16,077 --> 00:19:18,277
[JAKEN WHIMPERS]

323
00:19:38,685 --> 00:19:41,426
- THIS DRAGON
HAS GIVEN ME A GIFT.

324
00:19:41,459 --> 00:19:45,693
NOW I CAN GO BACK
AND CLAIM WHAT IS OWING TO ME.

325
00:19:45,726 --> 00:19:48,193
TETSUSAIGA.

326
00:20:00,528 --> 00:20:02,828
[GROANING]

327
00:20:03,476 --> 00:20:06,043
- FAREWELL!
- YOU'RE LEAVING US?

328
00:20:06,076 --> 00:20:07,810
YOU'RE HEADING OUT ALONE?

329
00:20:07,843 --> 00:20:11,110
- WELL, INUYASHA'S
NOT MUCH PROTECTION FOR ME.

330
00:20:11,143 --> 00:20:12,376
- COME ON.
- LET HIM GO.

331
00:20:12,410 --> 00:20:17,343
WHO NEEDS HIM?
THE OLD GEEZER WOULD ONLY
SLOW US DOWN ANYWAY.

332
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:21,176
- HMM!
GIVE IT BACK.

333
00:20:21,210 --> 00:20:23,243
THE TETSUSAIGA IS USELESS
IN YOUR HANDS.

334
00:20:23,276 --> 00:20:25,243
IT WOULD BE BETTER OFF
AS SCRAP METAL.

335
00:20:25,276 --> 00:20:28,643
- I TOLD YA,
DON'T TOUCH MY SWORD.

336
00:20:28,676 --> 00:20:30,943
- INUYASHA!

337
00:20:30,976 --> 00:20:33,776
- DON'T SAY I DIDN'T WARN YOU.

338
00:20:34,143 --> 00:20:35,843
- HE'S NOT AFRAID
TO SPEAK HIS MIND.

339
00:20:35,876 --> 00:20:41,010
- EITHER TOTO-SAI IS EXTREMELY
BRAVE OR HE'S EXTREMELY SENILE.

340
00:20:41,043 --> 00:20:43,076
- THAT POOR LITTLE RUNT
OF THE DOG DEMON

341
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:45,732
IS GONNA GET HIMSELF KILLED
BY SESSHO-MARU.

342
00:20:45,765 --> 00:20:50,726
HE HASN'T EVEN BEEN ABLE
TO SEE THE WIND SCAR THAT
AWAKENS TETSUSAIGA'S POWER.

343
00:20:51,954 --> 00:20:54,320
- AREN'T YOU GONNA GO
AFTER HIM, INUYASHA?

344
00:20:54,354 --> 00:20:57,287
AFTER ALL, HE IS THE ONE
WHO MADE TETSUSAIGA.

345
00:20:57,320 --> 00:21:01,487
- HUH! YEAH, WELL,
THAT OLD FART IS FULL OF IT.

346
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,254
- HUH?

347
00:21:04,787 --> 00:21:07,620
- HE'S BACK.

348
00:21:08,854 --> 00:21:11,720
- AAAH! OOMPH!

349
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:18,387
- SESSHO-MARU!

350
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:23,020
- STAY WHERE YOU ARE,
OR I'LL TEAR YOU BOTH TO SHREDS.

351
00:21:23,054 --> 00:21:24,354
[WHIMPERING]

352
00:21:24,387 --> 00:21:26,787
DID YOU HEAR THAT?
I THINK WE'RE IN
BIG TROUBLE NOW.

353
00:21:26,820 --> 00:21:28,887
- LISTEN, OLD MAN,
YOU'VE GOT NO INTENTION

354
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:31,787
OF MAKING SESSHO-MARU
A NEW SWORD, NOW, DO YA?

355
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:32,620
- NO.

356
00:21:32,654 --> 00:21:33,620
- YOU HEAR THAT?

357
00:21:33,654 --> 00:21:36,987
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF THIS
BAD RAP OVER TETSUSAIGA,

358
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:39,120
AND NOW I'M ITCHIN'
TO USE IT AND FIGHT.

359
00:21:39,154 --> 00:21:43,220
SO, LET'S SETTLE THIS
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

360
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:48,420
- HAVE NO FEAR.
- UHH!

361
00:21:48,454 --> 00:21:50,887
- IT WILL ALL END TODAY.

362
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:53,454
YOU'LL NEVER HAVE
THE POWER TO BEAT ME,

363
00:21:53,487 --> 00:21:57,254
NOT WITHOUT THE WIND SCAR.

364
00:22:03,181 --> 00:22:05,648
[WOMAN SINGING IN JAPANESE]

365
00:23:38,754 --> 00:23:42,621
- INUYASHA'S FATHER HAS GIVEN
EACH OF HIS TWO SONS A SWORD.

366
00:23:42,654 --> 00:23:44,775
BUT THE OLDER BROTHER,
SESSHO-MARU,

367
00:23:44,808 --> 00:23:48,275
DOESN'T LIKE THE FACT
THAT INUYASHA HAS BEEN
GIVEN THE TETSUSAIGA.

368
00:23:48,308 --> 00:23:53,408
THE MYSTERY OF THE WIND SCAR
IS FINALLY REVEALED TO INUYASHA
IN BATTLE WITH HIS BROTHER.

369
00:23:53,442 --> 00:23:57,175
BUT SESSHO-MARU DRAWS
HIS SWORD, THE TENSEIGA.

370
00:23:57,208 --> 00:23:58,475
IT'S THE SWORD OF LIFE.

371
00:23:58,508 --> 00:24:01,075
SO, THEN, WHAT HAPPENS
TO SESSHO-MARU?

372
00:24:01,108 --> 00:24:02,389
NEXT ON "INUYASHA..."

373
00:24:04,697 --> 00:24:05,697
SEE YA SOON!

